Steps to Reproduce
1. Assess & Clean Dataset

Check missing values

Standardize text fields (Commodity, Market, Variety)

Convert Arrival_Date to date format

Export cleaned data to Data/cleaned/

2. Design Dashboard Mockups

Create layout in PPT/Canva/Figma

Decide KPI cards, charts, slicer positions

Save mockup to Visuals/

3. Build Power BI Dashboard & Data Model

Import cleaned dataset

Create DAX measures: Total Prices, Volatility %, Rankings, etc.

Build visualizations:

KPI Cards

Bar Charts

Line Trend Chart

Donut Chart

Max vs Min Comparison

Price Stability

Detailed Table

Format theme & interactions

4. Export Reports & Prepare Analysis Report

Export PBIX → PDF report

Add screenshots and document insights

Finalize analysis report in Reports/

Key Insights / Learnings

Black Pepper, Arecanut, and Coconut Oil dominate Kerala’s market volume.

Modal price trends show significant fluctuations across years (high seasonality).

Arecanut and Pepper show extremely high price volatility (unstable pricing).

Cashewnuts, Pepper garbled have more stability compared to spices.

Dataset reveals strong market dependency on certain commodities.

Power BI’s DAX calculations help uncover price gaps and ranking insights.
